text.section:
Subject to subsection (c) of this section, a court:
may suspend a sentence generally or for a definite time;
may pass orders and impose terms as to costs, recognizance for appearance, or matters relating to the residence or conduct of the defendant who is convicted as may be deemed proper;
may order confinement in any care or custody as may be deemed proper; or
may order a person to a term of custodial confinement as a condition of a suspended sentence.
